Vice President Kamala Harris gave a speech at Bowie State University in Bowie, Maryland, discussing the importance of homeownership and announcing a reduction in mortgage insurance payments for new FHA homeowners. She shared a personal story about her mother's journey to homeownership and emphasized the significance of owning a home in building wealth and community. Harris also highlighted the work done by the Department of Housing and Urban Development to expand access to housing and counseling. She spoke about the challenges faced by homeowners during the pandemic and the actions taken by the Biden administration to provide relief. The reduction in mortgage insurance payments is aimed at helping more people, especially first-time homebuyers, achieve homeownership. Harris emphasized that lowering costs for working people is essential for the prosperity of the nation.